<script>
$(function() {
  $('a[href*="#"]:not([href="#"])').click(function() {
    if (location.pathname.replace(/^\//,'') == this.pathname.replace(/^\//,'') && location.hostname == this.hostname) {
      var target = $(this.hash);
      target = target.length ? target : $('[name=' + this.hash.slice(1) +']');
      if (target.length) {
        $('html, body').animate({
          scrollTop: target.offset().top
        }, 1000);

        $('#stocks').hide(0).fadeIn(100).removeClass('hidden');
        return false;
      }
    }
  });
});


$(function() {
	$('#anchor1').click(function() {
    var href = $.attr(this, 'href');
    $('html, body').animate({
        scrollTop: $(href).offset().top
    }, 500, function () {
        window.location.hash = href;
    });
    $('#funds').hide(0).fadeIn(100).removeClass('hidden');
    return false;
	});
});

  </script>

<div class="edu-block">
  <div class="big-headline">
  There are 2 main ways to invest in the stock market:
  </div>
  <div class="headline">
	<ul>
		<li>buy a specific company's stock</li>
		<li>buy index funds</li>
	</ul>
	<p>We believe index funds are the best place to start. </p>
	<p>Would you like to know more about the tradeoffs between these two?</p>
  </div>


<br /><a href="#anchor" class="next-button">Yes</a><br /><br />

<%= form_for @investing_profile, url: wizard_path, method: :put do |f| %>
	<%= f.hidden_field :explain_stocks_vs_funds, value: "No" %>

	<%= f.submit "No", class:"next-button" %>
<% end %>
</div>

<div id="stocks" class="hidden" style="display:none;">
	<div class="edu-block"> <a name="anchor"></a>
	  <div class="big-headline">Investing in a specific company's stock
		</div>
		<div class="headline">
			<p>If you invest in a specific company, your money will go up and down following the company's ups and downs. </p>

			<p>The Good: it can be really fun to research and speculate on companies. And this can sometimes lead to big rewards!</p>

			<p>The Bad: this can also lead to big losses! Also, individual stocks tend to require more time and research than funds.</p>

			<p><span style="font-weight:500;">Main takeaway: this is a risky type of investment. </span>
			<br />Because of this, we don't recommend starting here or putting all of your money into individual stocks.</p>
		</div>

	<p><a href="#anchor1">Continue</a></p>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="funds" class="hidden" style="display:none;">
	<div class="edu-block">
		<a name="anchor1"></a><div class="big-headline">Investing in index funds
		</div>
		<div class="headline">
			<p>An index fund is a collection of company stocks. </p>

			<p>The Good: Index funds lower your risk by investing your money in a range of companies so you're not dependent on any one company's success or failure. Index funds also require less time and energy to manage than individual stocks.</p>

			<p>The Bad: Some would say it's less exciting than investing in individual stocks - there are fewer swings up and down. We think it's great to have less drama! But it's important to understand that some people might consider it a bit more "dull."</p>
		</div>
		 <div class="button-row">
    		<%= link_to "Got it", next_wizard_path, class:"next-button" %>
  		</div>
	</div>
</div>
